  "suggestion": "The plateau reflects full exploitation of the current design space under static fitness rules and fixed world structure. Beauty and survival are being optimized independently with diminishing returns on the composite score. The system needs structural novelty — new units of selection (colonies), new fitness signals (emergent complexity), or new environmental degrees of freedom (adaptive physics) — to escape local optima and discover qualitatively different evolutionary strategies.; [hard] Enable symbiosis and colony-level fitness computation. Allow organisms to form energy-sharing networks where survival and beauty scores are computed on the colony as a single unit, not individuals. Individual cells optimize for group phenotype. — Plateau suggests individual-level optimization is saturated. Collective behavior unlocks new beauty dimensions (symmetry across connected organisms, emergent patterns) and survival strategies (distributed resilience). Selection pressure shifts from maximizing individual traits to creating multi-agent coherence — a fundamentally different fitness landscape.; [medium] Redefine beauty as a dynamic property: measure it as the information density and topological variance of organism structure relative to local environment entropy. Remove static beautyScore; compute beauty emergently from how much organized complexity an organism maintains against environmental noise. — Static beautyScore is likely fully exploited (organisms have found the local optimum for the metric). Dynamic, context-dependent beauty creates a co-evolutionary arms race: as organisms get more beautiful, the environment's 'difficulty' adjusts, preventing plateau. Beauty becomes about adaptation strategy, not fixed traits.; [hard] Introduce adaptive world physics: let nutrient distribution, light intensity, viscosity, and interaction forces co-evolve with organism population. World properties drift slowly based on dominant organism morphologies, creating a non-stationary fitness landscape. — Current world is static — organisms converge to local optima within fixed rules. Adaptive physics means the environment becomes progressively 'harder' as organisms optimize it, preventing plateau. Organisms must evolve not just to survive current world, but to predict and adapt to how world changes based on collective behavior.",
